speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(455,81,'Introduction','It’s very hard to escape from WWII when visiting Berlin because the scars left from the Battle of Berlin are still evident 70 years on. So I strongly suggest you to go for a WWII tour as well as a Potsdam (their monarchy) tour to really get to know the city and its people. WWII was an anomaly in its long history.'),(466,109,'VAT','€175.01|20%'),(475,93,'VAT','£30|20%'),(476,89,'VAT','2,001 CZK|21%'),(477,81,'VAT','€25|19%'),(482,93,'Introduction','Everyone has their own interpretation on touring London from your friend’s or family’s input. So you will likely have your itinerary fixed before seeing this. Just want to add that this city is like really expensive'),(483,89,'Introduction','Very similar to Budapest but I found Budapest a little nicer and the food slightly better. Overall, Prague is still very affordable as compared to the rest of Europe and still has that charming old city feel. Also, its Old Town Square is one of the nicest I’ve seen'),(494,78,'VAT','100 TRY|18%'),(495,78,'Introduction','Istanbul was named the Top Destination according to a tripadvisor poll but I found most of the attractions a bit expensive. The food is different, in a good way. Also, the country is split between the European side and Asian side, just something to know.'),(496,72,'Introduction','The most touristy city on this list. Just about every popular site is so crowded with other tourists so just be prepared to rub shoulders. Other than that, the ruins feels underwhelming when comparing to those in Athens, maybe because the officials chose not to reproduce them and leaving them as-is. Also, you probably heard enough stories about the robberies and thieveries, so just be vigilant, don’t bring unnecessary cards and tie down if possible<br>\r\n<br>One more thing, your EU resident card/student card isn’t going to work. You need to be an EU citizen for discounts'),(503,72,'VAT','€155|22%'),(510,64,'VAT','€155|22%'),(511,64,'Introduction','I read Dan Brown’s Inferno before arriving hence I was especially excited for this trip. Other than the walking tour, the city did not disappoint. The view at Piazza Michelangelo is probably the best panoramic view among all the cities because the iconic buildings really stand out. The view of the Duomo from the Bell Tower is also something special. <br><br>\r\nWhile not as popular as other Italian cities, Florence may be its best.'),(514,56,'VAT','€155|22%'),(515,56,'Introduction','I went during the opening of the World Expo so the city was definitely buzzing more than usual with performances from Andrea Bocelli outside the Duomo to all the various tents set up for the event. Overall, I liked Milan more than I thought I would, probably only because of the World Expo.'),(516,51,'VAT','52,001 HUF|27%'),(517,51,'Introduction','Truth be told, the only thing we heard about Budapest prior to visiting was Wes Anderson’s <em>The Grand Budapest Hotel</em> which, as it turns out, wasn’t even filmed in Budapest. But that did not matter because the city is still very lovable. The food is definitely one of the best, with their full slate of meat on their menu. The place is also one of the cheaper ones so stock up on your groceries there. <br><br>\r\nOne more thing, it certainly seems like their hairdressing industry is pretty strong there so you can definitely find a cheap barber with your standard cut-wash-blow service.'),(520,51,'Transport','In-city Travel	|T10 equivalent	|3000HUF	|http://www.bkk.hu/en/prices/|\r\nAirport Transfer	|Requires 2 tickets.<br> One for the train to the bus terminal and the second to take the airport bus from the terminal	|600HUF|http://www.bud.hu/english/passengers/access_and_parking/by_public_transportation'),(523,46,'Accommodation','Hostel	|Along the outskirt of the inner city and just opposite <em>Naschmarkt</em> and about 3-4 stations from the train station (<em>Westbahnhof</em>)	<br>Has a free walking tour too!	|http://www.wombats-hostels.com/vienna/the-naschmarkt/|\r\nOther areas	|Anywhere near the inner city is great of course'),(524,46,'Introduction','Visited the city carrying really high expectations because my brother, father, and even grandfather said the city is very beautiful. I must say, having a single monarchy for such a long time really helped contribute to the elegant landscape of Vienna (the Austrian Parliament Building especially). However, it is too expensive for me. Also, walking aimlessly without a guide hampered my appreciation of all the grandiose buildings in the city. <br><br>\r\nApparently Wombat Hostel has a free walking tour on certain days which I, unfortunately, had given a miss. Small regret'),(525,46,'VAT','€75.01|20%'),(526,43,'Introduction','Warsaw didn’t seem as endearing as Krakow. It took over as the capital of Poland from Krakow in the late 16th century so it isn’t as charming and isn’t as historically relevant as Krakow. That being said, it is still very liveable with cheap food and consumables. However, if you are choosing between Warsaw and Krakow, always go for Krakow (its geographical location relative to other European cities is also better than Warsaw)'),(527,43,'VAT','200 PLN|23%'),(530,43,'Accommodation','Airbnb|The listing is no longer available. It was near the National Stadium east of the Vistula river. ||Other areas|Near the train station is good. <br> It is near the commercial heart of the city as well|'),(535,38,'VAT','€90.15|21%'),(536,38,'Introduction','Madrid has a more regal feel over Barcelona. Its buildings look stately and impressive but the city doesn’t feel as happening as Barcelona. Shopping-wise, it’s streets along Gran Via and Callao are more conventional compared to the hipster stuff in the alleys of Barcelona. It is difficult to say which is better so just go to both'),(541,33,'VAT','€90.15|21%'),(542,33,'Accommodation','Airbnb	|Within walking distance from La Rambla so it’s good enough I’ll say. The building is old though	|https://www.airbnb.com.sg/rooms/6308769?s=i2Ob|\r\nOther areas	|The more central areas of the city are Placa de Catalunya, along La Rambla, and maybe Plaza de Espana(nearer to the train station)|'),(549,33,'Introduction','Its dual identity of Spain vs Catalan makes the city more complex than its beaches and football teams. Hence, to really understand the city and the rivalry involved in each El Classico, the Walking tour is a great introduction. <br>Of course, if you’re not really into such stuff, admiring the beaches and whimsical Gaudi-an architecture is perfectly fulfilling too'),(550,25,'VAT','200 PLN|23%'),(551,25,'Introduction','Certainly did not expect myself to love this city as much as I did. Just about every aspect of this city was great. The food is cheap and tasty, sites were fulfilling and at times life-changing, and the people were lovely and friendly. Please invest in at least 3 days for this city, more if you can afford.'),(560,4,'VAT','€120|23%'),(561,4,'Introduction','Definitely my top 2 favourite city together with Krakow, something I certainly did not expect considering all the negativity surrounding the country at the moment. However, the sites, food, and feel of the city really stood out for me. Unlike the ruins in Rome, Athens chose to work on restoring them to their former glory hence the Acropolis will only get better in time. The food is cheap and amazing with the Mediterranean palate. The sites are incredibly student-friendly where the only paid site was the Panathenaic Stadium.\r\n<br>Likewise, invest in at least 3 days for this city.'),(564,109,'Water','true'),(565,93,'Water','true'),(566,89,'Water','true'),(567,81,'Water','true'),(568,56,'Water','true'),(569,64,'Water','true'),(570,72,'Water','true'),(571,51,'Water','true'),(572,46,'Water','true'),(574,38,'Water','true'),(575,33,'Water','true'),(576,4,'Water','true'),(577,43,'Subheading','A city still finding its feet'),(578,218,'_edit_last','1'),(579,218,'_edit_lock','1439743765:1'),(580,239,'_edit_last','1'),(581,239,'_edit_lock','1439720693:1'),(582,239,'Accommodation','Airbnb	|Very near to Fosshotel Baron which quickly became the main pickup and contact point. A 10/11 conveniently placed just opposite the apartment|https://www.airbnb.com.sg/rooms/2755880|\r\nOther areas	|It will be best to stay in a hotel because most tour group will pick you up from hotels. If your airbnb apartment has a hotel nearby, it may be able to fulfil this criteria. Lastly, having a kitchen is very important for costs cutting||Other parts of the country	|Logistically challenging but absolutely necessary if you want to tour the island. <br>You can consider getting a caravan but bear in mind that you can’t shower in those|'),(583,239,'Food','Cooking	|Their convenience store is called 10/11. I suggest cooking yourself because the cost of living in Iceland is really very high		|<placeholder></placeholder>|'),(584,239,'Introduction','The country is really beautiful. But the thing is, the locals know it too and they also know that people are willing to pay for it. So really do try to share a car together and try to prepare your own food. Icelandair allows you to check in your luggage so bring your consumables along. Lastly, you don’t need to change too much ISK because credit card is accepted everywhere (except the walking tour).<br><br>\r\nThat being said, Iceland is the best place for landscape and other natural wonders'),(585,239,'Moneyscale','4'),(586,239,'Subheading','\"Pure. Natural. Unspoiled. Iceland. The Way Life Should Be\"'),(587,239,'Transport','In-city Travel	|There’s public transportation within Reykjavik. But let’s face it, you are not gonna stay in the city for long		|<placeholder></placeholder>|http://s.straeto.is/timetableplanner/captureServiceDetails.do?method=reset&hss=0B6Ru179050405|\r\nCar rental	|See <em>Car Rental </em>in <em>Activities</em>|<placeholder></placeholder>||		\r\nAirport Transfer	|Flybus: either to the bus terminal or to hotels in Reykjavik	|1950ISK to terminal, 2500ISK to hotel	|https://www.re.is/flybus/||\r\n	Gray Line: direct to hotels in Reykjavik 	|2400ISK	|http://www.airportexpress.is/||\r\n	Public Transportation	|1600ISK	|http://s.straeto.is/timetableplanner/captureServiceDetails.do?method=reset&hss=0B6Ru179050405'),(588,239,'VAT','6000 ISK|24%'),(589,239,'Water','true'),(592,239,'Thumbnail','http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/IMG_20150213_130751.jpg'),(601,245,'_wp_attached_file','2015/08/IMG_20150213_153401.jpg'),(602,245,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:3262;s:6:\"height\";i:1472;s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"2015/08/IMG_20150213_153401.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:4:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"IMG_20150213_153401-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"IMG_20150213_153401-300x135.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:135;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:5:\"large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:32:\"IMG_20150213_153401-1024x462.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1024;s:6:\"height\";i:462;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:14:\"post-thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:31:\"IMG_20150213_153401-604x270.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:604;s:6:\"height\";i:270;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:2.399999999999999911182158029987476766109466552734375;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:7:\"Nexus 5\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1423841641;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:4:\"3.97\";s:3:\"iso\";s:3:\"100\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:18:\"0.0008467400508044\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(603,239,'Banner photo','http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/IMG_20150213_153401.jpg'),(606,247,'_edit_last','1'),(607,247,'_edit_lock','1439720692:1'),(608,247,'Accommodation','Hostel		|Fantastic location		|http://www.booking.com/hotel/se/birka-hostel.en-gb.html|\r\nOther areas	|-	<em>T-Centralen</em>, <em>Hotorget</em>, <em>Gamla Stan</em>, <em>Kungsträdgården</em> and <em>Östermalmstorg</em> are all great<br>\r\n-	Any further from the city and you probably have to take the metro |'),(609,247,'Food','Pizzeria BirkaPunkten	|Near St Eriksplan which was where I stayed. Great value for money considering the free flow biscuit and salad. One pizza is definitely good for two	|79SEK / pizza	|http://www.birkapunkten.nu/|\r\nKajsas Fisk	|Another great value for money eatery near the Concert House near T-Centralen. Must try<br>\r\nCheck their opening hours though	|95SEK/bowl	|http://www.tripadvisor.com.sg/Restaurant_Review-g189852-d929129-Reviews-Kajsas_Fisk-Stockholm.html|\r\nJensen’s Bofhus	|Franchise around the Scandinavian region. <br>Their lunch menu steak is pretty attractive	|50-80SEK	|'),(610,247,'Introduction','Stockholm was the city where I had my exchange so I think of it from a different point of view as I do other cities.<br><br> \r\nOverall, Stockholm is very expensive, its history isn’t even that long and it’s extremely cold. But what I found in Stockholm after just 5 months was an intimate sense of belonging, a rare respect for privacy and personal space, and a completely foreign yet strangely calming way of life. Must be the Scandinavian lifestyle!'),(611,247,'Moneyscale','4'),(612,247,'Subheading','The Capital of Scandinavia'),(613,247,'Transport','In-city Travel|	Oyster card style. <br>Very expensive to travel around so you probably want to stay somewhere central to minimise on the use of public transportion|	36SEK/trip<br>\r\n115SEK/24hours	|http://sl.se/en/fares--tickets/|\r\nAirport Transfer	|Arlanda to City by <em>Arlanda Express</em><br>\r\nStudent tickets sold over counters	|140SEK for students	|https://www.arlandaexpress.com/fares.aspx||\r\n	Arlanda to City via <em>Flygbussarna</em>	|99SEK online	|http://www.flygbussarna.se/en||\r\n	Skavsta to City via <em>Flygbussarna</em>	|139SEK online	||